{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2019-07-22-note-utility","webpackCompilationHash":"c4b2ef2e12dd622acf4c","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I just made a fun command-line function to easily create markdown notes from the command line.</p>\n<p>It creates a new file with a name like <code class=\"language-text\">note_2019-07-22.md</code>, apends a timestamp to it, and opens it in a text editor.</p>\n<p>The editor defaults to <code class=\"language-text\">vim</code> but can also be <code class=\"language-text\">code</code> (for vscode), or whatever you like. If you chose <code class=\"language-text\">vim</code> (or <code class=\"language-text\">vi</code>) it will automatically put you at the end of the file.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">note</code></p>\n<p><em>(defaults to <code class=\"language-text\">vim</code>)</em></p>\n</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">note code</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">note vim</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>I named it \"note\".</p>\n<h2 id=\"source\"><a href=\"#source\" aria-label=\"source permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Source</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function-name function\">note</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">fileName</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"note_<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">date</span> +%F<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>.md\"</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">date</span> +%c<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$fileName</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"========================\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$fileName</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$fileName</span>\n    <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$fileName</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">editor</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">${1<span class=\"token operator\">:-</span>\"vi\"}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">case</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">$editor</span>\"</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">in</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"vi\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">editor_args</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"+$\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"vim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">editor_args</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"+$\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    *<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">editor_args</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">esac</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token variable\">$editor</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$editor_args</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$fileName</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"example-usage\"><a href=\"#example-usage\" aria-label=\"example usage permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Example Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ note vim</code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>(editor opens)</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ ls\nnote_2019-07-22.md\n\n$ cat note_2019-07-22.md\nMon Jul 22 01:13:28 2019\n========================</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"date":"July 22, 2019","path":"/2019-07-22-note-utility","title":"A fun little CLI utility for writing markdown notes","tags":["programming","shell","cli","markdown"],"youtube":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false}